      "section_title": "How to Write a Research Paper",
      "subsection_id": "sec_01_05",
      "subsection_title": "Key Insights and Takeaways",
      "text": "Section: How to Write a Research Paper\nSubsection: Key Insights and Takeaways\nTags: writing process, paper structure, efficiency, writer's block\nContent: Writing order matters: Writing 'inside out' (Methods → Results → Conclusion → Introduction) is far more efficient than linear writing. Preparation is crucial: Completing all data analysis, figures, and tables before writing saves time and reduces frustration. Transparent limitations: Openly discussing study limitations strengthens the paper by anticipating reviewer concerns. Formulaic conclusion: Following a structured conclusion format streamlines writing and enhances clarity. Iterative refinement: Accept imperfect first drafts and polish over time to overcome perfectionism and writer's block. Introduction last: Writing the introduction last ensures it is targeted and relevant after the rest of the paper is drafted.\nKey points: Inside"
