      "text": "might inform action or decision-making. The introduction should engage the reader by explaining why the topic matters now— the urgency or significance of the debate. Typical structure: Context and relevance, Gaps and debates, Purpose and scope. Writing the introduction last ensures clarity and coherence since the review's findings and structure are fully formed.\nKey points: Write conclusion before introduction; Conclusion components: Summary, Limitations, Future directions, Implications; Introduction components: Context, Gaps, Purpose; Writing intro last ensures coherence"
    },
