      "section_title": "Manuscripts and Publishing Process",
      "subsection_id": "sec_03_01",
      "subsection_title": "Introduction to Manuscripts and Importance of Publishing",
      "text": "Section: Manuscripts and Publishing Process\nSubsection: Introduction to Manuscripts and Importance of Publishing\nTags: manuscript, publishing, submission, journal selection\nContent: A manuscript traditionally refers to any document written by hand or typewritten, as opposed to mechanically printed or reproduced automatically. Publishing a research paper is crucial because: It enhances public understanding of a research question. It establishes the author as an expert in their field of knowledge. Peer-reviewed publications provide evidence for evaluating the merit of research funding requests.\nKey points: Manuscript: handwritten or typewritten document; Enhances public understanding; Establishes author expertise; Supports funding requests"
    },
