      "subsection_title": "Manuscript Composition and Components",
      "text": "Section: Manuscripts and Publishing Process\nSubsection: Manuscript Composition and Components\nTags: manuscript, publishing, submission, journal selection\nContent: Once finalized, the draft becomes a manuscript, generally consisting of: Preliminary material, Body of the text, Reference list. For beginners, focus is placed on the preliminary material, which includes: Title (Should be concise, comprehensive, attractive, and specifically highlight the paper's focus), Authors (Author order indicates contribution; the first author contributed the most, others might be supervisors, co-researchers, or collaborators), Affiliations (Institutions where research was conducted; multiple affiliations are possible), Corresponding author (The primary contact for journal communication, listed on the front page or as a footnote), Keywords (Four to six selected words to facilitate retrieval of the research"
    },
