      "text": "Section: Manuscripts and Publishing Process\nSubsection: Body of Manuscript and Key Sections\nTags: manuscript, publishing, submission, journal selection\nContent: The body includes: Abstract, Introduction, Materials and Methods, Results and Discussion, Conclusion and Recommendations, Tables and Figures. The reference list is the final major component. A good manuscript typically has the following characteristics: Original and plagiarism-free content, Correct research methodology, including sampling design and statistical tools, Contribution to existing scientific knowledge, Ethical considerations addressed, Proper, effective writing style.\nKey points: Body sections: Abstract, Intro, Methods, Results, Discussion, Conclusion; Original and plagiarism-free; Correct methodology; Ethical considerations addressed"
    },
