      "section_title": "Manuscripts and Publishing Process",
      "subsection_id": "sec_03_04",
      "subsection_title": "Journal Selection: Factors to Consider",
      "text": "Section: Manuscripts and Publishing Process\nSubsection: Journal Selection: Factors to Consider\nTags: manuscript, publishing, submission, journal selection\nContent: Selecting an appropriate journal requires in-depth research and careful consideration. Important factors to look for in a journal: Relevant to the researcher's discipline or area, Peer-reviewed by experts, Has an International Standard Serial Number (ISSN) for electronic and print formats, Indexed in a globally or nationally recognized database, Included in the UGC CARE list (especially relevant for Indian researchers), Journal has a history of at least 8 to 10 volumes (indicates stability and credibility), Authentic publishing house, Transparent fee structure (some charge, some do not).\nKey points: Relevant to discipline; Peer-reviewed and Indexed; Has ISSN; UGC CARE list inclusion; History of 8-10 volumes; Transparent fee st"
    },
    {
