      "subsection_title": "Journal Selection: Factors to Avoid",
      "text": "Section: Manuscripts and Publishing Process\nSubsection: Journal Selection: Factors to Avoid\nTags: manuscript, publishing, submission, journal selection\nContent: Researchers should avoid journals that: Have poor quality or lack rigorous peer review, Do not follow standard publishing practices, Are not included in recognized indexing or UGC CARE lists, Are categorized as predatory or 'D3' journals, Demand immediate payments upon submission, Promise unrealistically fast publication (within a few days).\nKey points: Avoid poor quality or lack of peer review; Avoid non-indexed journals; Avoid predatory or 'D3' journals; Avoid immediate payment demands; Avoid unrealistic fast publication promises"
    },
