      "subsection_id": "sec_03_06",
      "subsection_title": "Manuscript Preparation According to Journal Guidelines",
      "text": "Section: Manuscripts and Publishing Process\nSubsection: Manuscript Preparation According to Journal Guidelines\nTags: manuscript, publishing, submission, journal selection\nContent: After selecting a journal, the manuscript must be formatted per the journal's author guidelines found on the journal's website. Key formatting aspects to adjust: Font type, size, and spacing, In-text citation style (e.g., author-year system or numbered references in superscript or brackets), Reference list formatting and completeness (all cited in text must appear in the list and vice versa), Preparation and numbering of tables and figures, and their placement (within the text or at the end). Each journal has unique formatting requirements, so careful adherence is essential.\nKey points: Follow journal author guidelines; Adjust font, size, spacing; Match citation style; Format references and tables/figures corre"
    },
