      "text": "Section: Manuscripts and Publishing Process\nSubsection: Manuscript Submission Process\nTags: manuscript, publishing, submission, journal selection\nContent: Researchers must follow instructions on: File format (single Word file, PDF, or section-wise files), Submission mode: either via email or through a journal's online portal (requiring registration and login). Along with the manuscript, additional documents may be required, including: Cover letter (Explains purpose of submission, addressed to the editor), Declaration letter (Confirms manuscript has not been published elsewhere), Suggested reviewers (Some journals ask authors to recommend 2-3 expert reviewers), Funding information (Discloses financial support for the research), Author contributions (Brief professional details or roles of contributing authors), Copyright form (Signed by all authors to transfer copyright, mandatory either a"
