      "text": "Section: Manuscripts and Publishing Process\nSubsection: Detailed Submission Steps\nTags: manuscript, publishing, submission, journal selection\nContent: The submission process is divided into multiple steps: Step 1: Enter the title and abstract of the manuscript. Step 2: Upload the manuscript files, including tables and figures. Step 3: Add co-authors and their affiliations. Step 4: Provide additional manuscript details such as: Number of words, Number of figures, Number of tables. Step 5: Review all entered information carefully. The system generates a PDF version of the manuscript for proofreading. Add keywords relevant to your research. Attach a cover letter for submission. Authors must proofread the generated PDF and correct any mistakes before final submission. Once satisfied, the author clicks submit to officially send the manuscript to the journal.\nKey points: Enter title and abstra"
