      "section_title": "Manuscript Writing and Structure (IMRD)",
      "subsection_id": "sec_04_03",
      "subsection_title": "Methods Section Details",
      "text": "Section: Manuscript Writing and Structure (IMRD)\nSubsection: Methods Section Details\nTags: IMRD, scientific writing, manuscript structure, six S's\nContent: The Methods section explains the research process in clear, stepwise detail, providing: Study setting and context (important for international readers). Study design. Operational definitions. Sampling strategy and sample size. Study procedures (data collection, investigations). Data management (collection and analysis). Ethical considerations and human participant protections. Methods vary by study design but must provide transparency and reproducibility to ensure credibility.\nKey points: Study setting and context; Study design and operational definitions; Sampling strategy and size; Data management and procedures; Ethical considerations; Ensure transparency and reproducibility"
    },
