      "section_title": "Manuscript Writing and Structure (IMRD)",
      "subsection_id": "sec_04_04",
      "subsection_title": "Results Section Details",
      "text": "Section: Manuscript Writing and Structure (IMRD)\nSubsection: Results Section Details\nTags: IMRD, scientific writing, manuscript structure, six S's\nContent: The Results section is typically the briefest, focused solely on what was found without interpretation. Results may be presented using: Text, Tables, Figures, Graphs, Images. Authors must avoid repeating information and adhere strictly to journal guidelines on the number and types of displays. Interpretation is reserved for the Discussion section.\nKey points: Focused on findings without interpretation; Use Text, Tables, Figures, Graphs, Images; Avoid repeating information; Adhere to journal guidelines on displays"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": 40,
