      "subsection_id": "sec_04_05",
      "subsection_title": "Discussion Section Details",
      "text": "Section: Manuscript Writing and Structure (IMRD)\nSubsection: Discussion Section Details\nTags: IMRD, scientific writing, manuscript structure, six S's\nContent: The Discussion section is described as the most important and intellectually demanding part, where the researcher: Summarizes key findings briefly (not more than three lines). Offers interpretations and inferences. Compares findings with existing literature (while avoiding overemphasis on comparisons). Key advice: Balance between comparing with literature and emphasizing your own interpretations—this section reveals the researcher's independent thinking. Within the Discussion, also address: Strengths of the study, such as novel methodologies, design, or unique contexts. Limitations, reported honestly and with commentary on how they may affect results. Following this, provide: Conclusions: The central take-home message aligned with"
    },
