      "subsection_title": "Abstract and Keywords",
      "text": "Section: Manuscript Writing and Structure (IMRD)\nSubsection: Abstract and Keywords\nTags: IMRD, scientific writing, manuscript structure, six S's\nContent: Abstract is described as a miniature manuscript and the most commonly read part. It can be: Structured abstract (Divided into Introduction, Methods, Results, and Conclusions), Unstructured abstract (A summary without explicit subheadings), Plain language summary (For lay readers or the general public). Abstracts typically range from 100 to 350 words and require careful crafting since many readers base their decision to read further on the abstract. Keywords are critical for indexing and ensuring discoverability in search engines. Selecting correct and relevant keywords: Helps the article be found by targeted searches. Increases the likelihood of being read and cited.\nKey points: Abstract: Miniature manuscript; Types: Structured, Unstruc"
    },
