      "subsection_title": "References and Argument Matrix",
      "text": "Section: Manuscript Writing and Structure (IMRD)\nSubsection: References and Argument Matrix\nTags: IMRD, scientific writing, manuscript structure, six S's\nContent: References must credit all sources used, focusing on relevant and recent literature. Important points include: Use of reference management software to ease formatting. Awareness of different referencing styles such as Vancouver or Harvard. Proper in-text citations linked with reference lists at the manuscript end. IMRD structure and Argument Matrix, which: Organizes 2 or 3 central ideas logically across each manuscript section. Ensures continuity and flow of ideas from Introduction through Methods, Results, and Discussion. Helps maintain a linear and coherent narrative.\nKey points: Credit all sources; Use reference management software; Follow referencing styles (Vancouver/Harvard); Argument Matrix organizes central ideas across"
    },
