      "subsection_title": "Theses and Dissertations",
      "text": "Section: Manuscript Writing and Structure (IMRD)\nSubsection: Theses and Dissertations\nTags: IMRD, scientific writing, manuscript structure, six S's\nContent: A thesis is an extended, university-mandated document for postgraduate or doctoral degrees. It is primary research led by the scholar, guided by a mentor. Bound by university-specific guidelines. Can be converted into a manuscript for journal publication. Manuscripts and theses differ in length, word limits, target audience, and sometimes structure (thesis may include additional sections). Additional thesis-specific sections may include: Table of contents, List of abbreviations, List of tables and figures.\nKey points: Thesis: University-mandated document; Guided by mentor; Can be converted to manuscript; Differ in length and structure from manuscripts; May include Table of contents, Lists"
