      "section_id": "sec_05",
      "section_title": "Writing Peer Review Reports",
      "subsection_id": "sec_05_02",
      "subsection_title": "Step 1: Overview",
      "text": "Section: Writing Peer Review Reports\nSubsection: Step 1: Overview\nTags: peer review, reviewer guide, evaluation, feedback\nContent: Start the review by thanking the editors for the opportunity to review the paper, which is a customary academic practice. Provide a brief summary of the paper's topic and aims to demonstrate understanding and context. Example given: For a paper titled 'Virtual Reality and Digital Education: A Network of Forance Perspective on Effective Use,' an appropriate summary might be: The paper aims to enhance understanding of immersive technologies in digital learning. It reports results from an interview study and develops a theoretical framework to help educators integrate virtual reality into curricula.\nKey points: Thank editors; Provide brief summary of topic and aims; Demonstrate understanding"
    },
    {
      "chunk_id": 52,
      "section_id": "sec_05",
      "section_title": "Writing Peer Review Reports",
      "subsection_id": "sec_05_03",
      "subsection_title": "Step 2: State Your Expertise",
      "text": "Section: Writing Peer Review Reports\nSubsection: Step 2: State Your Expertise\nTags: peer review, reviewer guide, evaluation, feedback\nContent: Reviews are always anonymous, but it is important that editors and authors understand the reviewer's background and expertise. Include 1-2 sentences describing your relevant research experience to establish credibility. Mention how you will structure the review and if any aspects will be de-emphasized due to your expertise. Example: 'Having contributed to several studies in virtual reality myself, I consider my expertise significant. However, as I primarily use quantitative methods, I will focus less on methodology and ask editors to seek other reviewers' opinions on this.' This transparency helps editors contextualize your comments and complements the overall review process.\nKey points: State background and expertise; Establish credibility; Menti"
